Title: HR's role in corporate governance: Present and prospective
Author-Name: Beatty, Richard W.
Author-Name: Ewing, Jeffrey R.
Author-Name: Tharp, Charles G.
Abstract: Corporate wrongdoing is damaging investor confidence and tarnishing the credibility of the U.S. business community, guilty and innocent alike. Some misdeeds are clearly criminal, others simply unethical or damaging to reputations. They range from “massaging” numbers (“managed earnings”), which tests the limits of financial prudence, to outright fraud. Caught in the limelight are U.S. corporate giants representing some of the world's best-known brands and most famous CEOs, many only yesterday lionized in the business press.
