Title: When organizational relocation means family relocation: An emerging issue for strategic human resource management
Author-Name: Lawson, Marian B.
Abstract: Relocations of entire organizational units raise special family adjustment issues. This article reports on the reactions of employees and their families to such a relocation. Employees' adjustment was more strongly related to nonwork and family impacts of the move than to factors in the workplace. Adjustment was more difficult for families inexperienced in relocation, despite extensive company assistance programs.
